02/11/2006
ANKARA, Turkey -- Turkey and Greece are expected to hold a joint military drill from November 6th-10th aimed at tackling natural disasters.
The exercise will take place on Turkish territory and will be aimed at improving interoperability and boosting mutual trust.
On Thursday, meanwhile, authorities announced that the death toll from flash flooding in southeast Turkey climbed to 31 overnight.
Ten people, including seven young children, were swept away in the town of Batman alone.
(BBC - 2/11/06;
Zaman, NTV, Reuters, ERT - 01/11/06)
